=545  \\$aThe Poston Relocation Center in Arizona was the largest of the ten Japanese American internment camps operated by the United States War Relocation Authority during World War II, 1942-1945.
=520  \\$aRecords related to a community government formed by Japanese American internees at the Poston Relocation Center, Arizona, 1942-1945. Material includes reports from committees on health care, social welfare, and education, as well as a charter for the community government.  The collection also includes memoranda about camp governance and other publications in English and Japanese distributed by the United States War Relocation Authority, as well as contemporary newspaper clippings about relocation centers and Japanese Americans.
=561  \\$aPurchased from William Reese Co. on the William Robertson Coe Fund No. 3, 2010.
=546  \\$aChiefly in English; some items in Japanese.
